28/09/2003
BUCHAREST, Romania -- The General Direction for Fighting Organised Crime and Drugs completed a project Friday (26 September) for training 42 women in the Romanian police for identifying victims of human trafficking. The UNDP is providing technical and financial support for the initiative. Anti-crime authorities in Romania have identified and dismantled 190 networks and groups involved in human trafficking in since the beginning of the year. (Rompres - 27/09/03)
